search_parameters.q: Queen, age, music related skills + abilities + occupations, proficiency in each, and current residence location (city, state)

text_blocks.snippet: Since the term "Queen" can refer to several prominent figures, here are details for the most likely subjects:

list.snippet: Occupations: Rapper, singer, songwriter, actress, and producer.
Rapping: Expert; a hip-hop pioneer who released her debut album, All Hail the Queen, at age 19.
Singing: Highly proficient; transition from hip-hop to jazz and traditional pop.
Beatboxing: Early career skill; she began as a human beatbox for the group Ladies Fresh.
Current Residence: While she maintains properties in Los Angeles, CA, she primarily identifies with her hometown of East Orange, NJ.
Brian May (Guitarist): 78 years old. Expert guitarist, songwriter, and vocalist. Resides in London, UK.
Roger Taylor (Drummer): 76 years old. Multi-instrumentalist (drums, vocals, guitar). Resides in Surrey, UK.
John Deacon (Bassist - Retired): 74 years old. Expert bassist and songwriter. Resides in London, UK.
Freddie Mercury (Lead Singer): Deceased (1991). Was an expert vocalist and pianist.
Music Skills: Studied piano, flute, and clarinet as a child.
Current Residence: Copenhagen, Denmark, primarily at Amalienborg Palace.
Status: Deceased. She died at age 96 on September 8, 2022.
